Police have arrested four suspects in the Johannesburg CBD for impersonating police officers. Police recovered two fake appointment police certificates from the suspects aged between 27 – 45. Joburg police spokesperson Xoli Mbele says the suspects are expected to appear at the Johannesburg Magistrates Court on Monday… “They stopped three foreign nationals demanding passports. They told one of the victims that his passport has expired and demanded R3000. Police came to their rescue and apprehended the suspects. Police are on the ground to ensure that bogus police that is damaging the image of the police in the Johannesburg CBD are apprehended.